quran[26]{c,v,t}:
  23,93,"(The believer should) pray, \"My Lord! If you let me witness (in my life-time) what the wrongdoers are warned against"
  23,94,My Lord! Then let me not be among them
  23,95,"For, behold, We are Able to show you that against which they are warned"
  23,96,"(Nevertheless), counter evil with something that is better. We are best Aware of what others say and do"
  23,97,"And say, \"My Lord! I seek refuge with you from the prompting of the satanic forces of dissension (in my heart and among the enemy)"
  23,98,"And I seek refuge with you, my Lord, lest they come near me"
  23,99,"(Those who keep belying themselves), when death comes to one of them, say, \"My Lord! Send me back\" (2)"
  23,100,"That I may do good works in that I left behind! But, nay! It is a mere word of no significance that he speaks. And behind them is a barrier until the Day they are raised"
  23,101,"And when the Trumpet is blown, there will be no relationships between them that Day, nor will they ask about one another"
  23,102,Then those whose scales (of good deeds) are heavy; they are the successful
  23,103,"And those whose scales are light, it is they who have wasted their \"Self\", and abide in hell"
  23,104,Their faces in agony as the fire burns them therein
  23,105,"(And it will be said), \"Were not My Revelations conveyed to you, and did you not deny them"
  23,106,"They will say, \"Our Lord! Our misfortune overwhelmed us, and we became a people astray"
  23,107,"Our Lord! Bring us out of here, and if we return to our old behavior, then indeed we shall be wrongdoers"
  23,108,"He will say, \"Dump yourselves therein and plead not with Me"
  23,109,"Behold, there were among My servants such who used to say, 'Our Lord! We have come to believe, so forgive us and bestow Grace upon us, for, You are the Best of the merciful"
  23,110,"But you ridiculed them, to the extent that it made you forget My Message while you were laughing at them"
  23,111,This Day I have rewarded them for their patience. They verily are the triumphant
  23,112,"He will ask, \"What number of years have you spent on earth"
  23,113,"They will say, \"We stayed a day or part of a day. But ask those who keep count"
  23,114,"He will say, \"You stayed only a little, if you had only realized then"
  23,115,"Do you think that We have created you without purpose, and that you will not be brought before Us"
  23,116,"Know that Allah is Exalted, the King, the Truth. There is no god but He, the Lord of the Honored Throne"
  23,117,"Hence, anyone who calls upon gods besides Allah, has no evidence of it. And his account rests with his Lord? Verily, such deniers of the Truth will not attain the ultimate prosperity"
  23,118,"And say, \"My Lord! Grant me the protection of forgiveness absolving my imperfections and bestow Grace, for You are the Best of the merciful"